# Styling Rules

## Tokens
Use Tailwind tokens, never raw hex in JSX:
- `bg-bg`, `bg-surface`, `text-ink`, `text-muted`
- `text-accent`, `border-accent`, accent gradient for primary CTAs

Gradient utility for primary buttons/headlines:
`bg-gradient-to-br from-accent to-accent2`

## Fonts
- Headings: `font-display` (Syne), tracking tight (`tracking-tighter` on big headings).
- Labels/eyebrows/prices-cycle/stat-labels: `font-mono` (DM Mono).
- Eyebrow labels use a `//` prefix and uppercase, e.g. `// pricing`.

## Components
- Card surfaces: hairline border `border-white/[0.07]`, rounded `rounded-2xl`, subtle bg `bg-white/[0.03]`.
- Hover: lift (`-translate-y-1`) + accent border, smooth `transition`.
- Featured pricing card: accent top-border, tinted bg `bg-accent/[0.04]`, "Popular" pill.
- Use `cva` for Button and PricingCard variants.

## Layout
- Mobile-first. Base = mobile, scale with `md:` / `lg:`.
- Max content width ~1100px, centered, generous vertical rhythm.
- Background: subtle cyan grid + soft radial glow top-center (fixed, pointer-events-none, z-0).

## Motion
- Staggered fade-up on hero load via `animation-delay`.
- CSS transitions for hover. No heavy animation libraries.
- Custom cursor (dot + lagging ring) desktop-only; disable on touch/mobile.

## Accessibility
- AA contrast. Use `text-ink` for body, reserve `text-accent` for large text / borders / links.
- Visible focus rings. Real semantic elements. `alt` / `aria-label` always.
